"title": "1245: God of the fathers",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1245",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>God's particular association with Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, the fathers of the nations of Israel, highlights his faithfulness in fulfilling the promises made to them. He is the God who establishes a covenant with his people for their everlasting blessing.</p>\n<h2>God's relationship with the fathers</h2>\n<h3>The God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:32\">ACT 7:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:6\">EXO 3:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:15\">EXO 3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:5\">EXO 4:5</a></p>\n<h3>The God of Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps20:1\">PSA 20:1</a></strong> <em>“Jacob” is used here as a synonym for the nation of Israel. This usage is common in the Psalms as a reminder to God's people of his faithfulness to Jacob and the emergent nation of Israel.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen32:27-Gen32:28\">GEN 32:27–32:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:7\">PSA 14:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:7\">PSA 46:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps46:11\">PSA 46:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps75:9\">PSA 75:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps76:6\">PSA 76:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps114:7\">PSA 114:7</a></p>\n<h3>Such a relationship served as an encouragement to others</h3>\n<p>Abraham's servant was encouraged to trust God in his mission by the example of Abraham's faith:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:12\">GEN 24:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:27\">GEN 24:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:42\">GEN 24:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:48\">GEN 24:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:24\">GEN 26:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:42\">GEN 31:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen31:53\">GEN 31:53</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:1-Gen46:3\">GEN 46:1–46:3</a> <em>Jacob learned to fear and trust God through his father Isaac.</em></p>\n<h2>God's covenant with the fathers</h2>\n<h3>God's promises that they will be the fathers of a great nation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:13-Gen28:15\">GEN 28:13–28:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:2-Gen26:4\">GEN 26:2–26:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:16-Exod3:17\">EXO 3:16–3:17</a></p>\n<h3>God remembers and fulfils his promises</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:24\">EXO 2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:3-Exod6:5\">EXO 6:3–6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13\">EXO 32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:42\">LEV 26:42</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:8\">DEU 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:17\">ACT 7:17</a></p>\n<h3>God makes a covenant with his people to be their God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:12-Deut29:13\">DEU 29:12–29:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:7\">GEN 17:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:7-Exod6:8\">EXO 6:7–6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:8-Ps105:11\">PSA 105:8–105:11</a></p>\n<h2>Characteristics of the God of the fathers</h2>\n<h3>He blesses his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:11\">DEU 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut30:20\">DEU 30:20</a></p>\n<h3>He is powerful</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs18:36-1Kgs18:39\">1KI 18:36–18:39</a></p>\n<h3>He is gracious and compassionate</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs13:23\">2KI 13:23</a></p>\n<h3>He keeps his people faithful</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:18\">1CH 29:18</a></p>\n<h3>He gives wisdom</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:23\">DAN 2:23</a></p>\n<h3>He is the God of the living</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:32\">MAT 22:32</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:26-Mark12:27\">MRK 12:26–12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:37-Luke20:38\">LUK 20:37–20:38</a></p>\n<h2>People sometimes fail to respond to the God of their fathers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:3\">JOS 18:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:11\">NUM 32:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:10-Deut6:12\">DEU 6:10–6:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:27\">DEU 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:7\">2CH 30:7</a></p>",
